I want to watch movies this summer! In movie theatres! With no TV and my computer's DVD drive dead, I haven't seen a movie* in ages. And I haven't watched a movie in a movie theatre* in forever. I definitely want a TV in my living room someday, someday, someday† -- dunno about actually getting cable, I don't watch TV much -- but to watch movies on, in a dark room, curled up on a couch or some poufy cushions with my favouritest people, perhaps nomming popcorn.

* except Avatar and How To Train Your Dragon ... a million times each
† I also want an island in my kitchen. and a porch swing or hammock. also a real-wood-burning fireplace. and a big marble bathtub (as in not just the standard rectangular ones). and secret passageways, or at least hallways that lead to random rooms and make bemused guests wonder how they ended up there, and also rooms that you don't realize exist until you stumble upon them accidentally. and gauzy curtains and big bay windows with window seats and cushions. and a library!

I love Breezy Hill Farm pies. The first ingredient is always the filling -- if it's a blueberry pie, the main ingredient is fresh blueberries -- if it's a strawberry & rhubarb pie, the main ingredients are fresh strawberries and fresh rhubarb -- and you can definitely taste it, too. The next ingredient is flour, and there are eggs and some butter and stuff. Sugar is always near the end of the list. I haven't seen more than five or six ingredients total in any of their pies... and there are no preservatives -- I had an apple pie go bad after a week in the fridge! I need to get their larger pies, since they have a larger filling-to-crust ratio. I am able to demolish the larger half of one of their six-inch pies for lunch -- yum!
